tasks.description:
Schema updates for archive metadata tracking - REVISED for multi-agent/multi-user future.

## New Fields in Archived Task

### archivedBy (NEW - Multi-Agent/Multi-User Attribution)
```json
{
  "archivedBy": {
    "type": "string",
    "enum": ["user", "agent", "auto", "hook"],
    "description": "Actor type that performed the archive"
  },
  "archivedByIdentity": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Actor identity: git user, session ID, or policy name"
  },
  "archivedByGitUser": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Git user identity if available (e.g., 'Name <email>')"
  }
}
```

### archivedFrom (REVISED - Git Context)
```json
{
  "archivedFromBranch": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Git branch name at archive time"
  },
  "archivedFromCommit": {
    "type": "string",
    "description": "Git commit SHA at archive time"
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] archivedBy* fields added to archive schema
- [ ] archivedFrom* git context fields added
- [ ] archive.sh populates fields from git config and session
- [ ] Backward compatible (new fields optional)

## Future Value
- Multi-agent session tracking
- Multi-user collaboration audit trail
- Git-integrated task management provenance

Create comprehensive config schema for all analyze settings.

## Config Structure
```json
{
  "analyze": {
    "algorithm": "leverage_scoring_v2",
    "hierarchyWeights": {
      "parentChild": 0.3,
      "crossEpic": 1.0,
      "crossPhase": 1.5
    },
    "phaseBoost": {
      "current": 1.5,
      "adjacent": 1.25,
      "distant": 1.0
    },
    "sizeStrategy": "balanced",
    "sizeWeights": {
      "small": 1.0,
      "medium": 1.0,
      "large": 1.0
    },
    "lockAwareness": {
      "enabled": true,
      "staleThreshold": 300,
      "warnOnly": true
    },
    "staleDetection": {
      "enabled": true,
      "pendingDays": 30,
      "noUpdateDays": 14,
      "blockedDays": 7
    },
    "output": {
      "showCriticalPath": true,
      "showStaleWarnings": true,
      "showConcurrentWarnings": true,
      "maxRecommendations": 10
    }
  }
}
```

## Files
- schemas/config.schema.json
- lib/config.sh (add analyze config reading)
- scripts/analyze.sh (read config)

## Migration
- Add defaults for new config options
- Backward compatible with existing configs
